      • add

        void add(int index,
       E element)
        Adds (inserts) the specfied element at the specfied index of the list - note that it does not overwrite any existing data at that location. This method does allow adding to the first index beyond the end of the list. For example, if a list had a size of 10, the index 9 is its logical end but this method allows added an element at index 10.
        Parameters:
        index - The index to add (insert) the specfied element.
        element - The element to add (insert) to the speficfied position.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - when the specified index is negative or past the logical end of the list.
